Home / Primary & Specialty Care / Primary Care Services
Primary care physicians (PCP) at UI Health provide the care every member of your family needs at each stage of life.

Our primary care doctors perform routine health exams, such as physical exams, well-child visits, and well-woman visits; help you prevent or manage of chronic conditions like diabetes, high blood pressure, and asthma; and provide education about exercising, eating healthy, and other important steps you can take to be your healthiest self.
Partnering with a UI Health PCP is one of the most important things you can do for your health.
The Care You Need in a Way That Works for You
With virtual visits, seeing your UI Health provider is as simple as clicking a link in a text message. It’s never been more convenient to get the care you need to stay healthy.
Preventative Care for the Whole Family
At UI Health, we believe in preventive care for the whole family, from children to older adults.   Find the PCP that’s right for you.
Internal medicine physicians specialize in the prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of health issues that impact adults.
Family medicine doctors diagnose, treat, and help prevent disease for patients of all ages, from children to older adults.
Our general pediatricians provide preventative care that ensures children grow up healthy and develop properly.
Our team provides a variety of services for obstetric and gynecologic healthcare, including well-woman exams, family planning advice, prenatal care, and more.
The Two-Generation Clinic at UI Health allows women and children to receive all of the primary care services they need at the same place and time.
Our comprehensive team ensures older adults and their families have the education, support, and guidance they need to develop personalized care plans.

Home / Primary & Specialty Care / Primary Care Services / Our Services

Our primary care providers (PCP) act as your personal healthcare provider. Our experts from Family Medicine, Internal Medicine, Obstetrics & Gynecology, and Pediatrics treat patients of all ages, and we work together to manage all your family's healthcare needs, from treating common medical problems to caring for chronic medical conditions.

Our family medicine doctors take care of all your medicine needs: We provide a broad range of primary care services, including women's healthcare, immunizations, physicals, lab testing, medication refill, follow-up visits, and health counseling and education. We also have a Home Visits Program to provide medical care to patients of all ages without the need for hospitalization or an emergency visit.

The internal medicine specialists at UI Health are committed to helping you be the healthiest version of you. Our doctors focus on primary care, health maintenance, disease prevention and risk factors, and specialty care to provide you a personalized healthcare plan that fits your needs.

Our board-certified obstetricians and gynecologists focus on providing quality healthcare to girls, women, and expectant mothers. Whether you need a routine well-woman exam, family planning advice, or help with a gynecological condition, our OB/GYN team provides offer quality healthcare for women throughout their reproductive years and beyond.

The Department of Pediatrics delivers compassionate, personalized care to children of all ages, from infancy into young adulthood. We bring together primary and specialty pediatric care in one location. From well-child visits and immunizations in our clinics, to advanced care and emergency services on our designated pediatric hospital floor, we work with your family to address your medical and emotional concerns while providing the best care to your child. Our team helps manage chronic medical conditions and diseases to ensure your child grows up healthy and develops properly.
